Police are searching for two men who shot a security officer in Silverton, Pretoria, last Friday. Silverton police spokesperson Captain Jan Sepato said the men allegedly tried to force themselves into a casino in Pretoria Road. A scuffle ensued and the security officer was shot, Rekord East reported. The men then ran away. The police were notified and flagged down a Netcare 911 vehicle around 21:30 to treat the man. Paramedics treated the critically wounded man at the scene before taking him to hospital, said Netcare 911 spokesperson Chris Botha. Sepato said a docket for attempted murder was opened at the Silverton Police Station. He urged anyone with any information to contact Detective Constable Ditlake at Silverton police station. &#8211; Caxton News Service